race.comment: PAPER DOLL (10) has been in the money 4/6 so far and is bursting to win. Has been runner-up both starts this campaign and off the low draw gets a chance to get off the mark. CHICAGO KING (1) is another long overdue having placed at 9/13 starts. Trained here but surprisingly having first try at home. Has been winding up strongly and looks one of the leading hopes again. YOUMEANDDUPRE (8) is a progressive type yet to place in four starts but form is much better than it looks. Gave a sight fresh off a wide drawn but fitter again and drops in weight with the claim. Tricky gate again but fitter and will give a sight. SAMURAI WAND (4) has been going along okay on the Poly with placings the last two. Handles the soft going and fit and on home track. One of the chances.
